1 1. To maintain strong economic growth and to improve the
2 quality of life of its citizens, the electrical generation capacity
3 within the State of Oklahoma must increase significantly over time;
4 2. Much of this required generation capacity will, by
5 necessity, be provided by renewable energy projects that have a
6 significant footprint which could potentially impact agriculture
7 production;
8 3. There are strategies for both the siting and construction of
9 these renewable energy projects that could minimize this impact on
10 farming and ranching and in some cases assist in improving overall
11 agriculture productivity; and
12 4. It is in the interest of the public that the State of
13 Oklahoma develop a legislative strategy designed to encourage
14 renewable energy development in a way that works in harmony with
15 farming and ranching.
16 B. It is the intent of the Legislature that policies designed
17 to provide for new renewable energy generation construction also
18 supports the agriculture industry to be developed in the future.
