1 SECTION 3. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
2 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 851 of Title 17, unless there is
3 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
4 A. There is hereby created the Oklahoma Agrivoltaics Advisory
5 Committee. The Committee shall consist of the following seventeen
6 (17) members:
7 1. The Secretary of Agriculture or designee;
8 2. The Secretary of Energy and Environment or designee;
9 3. The Director of the Oklahoma Conservation Commission or
10 designee;
11 4. The Director of the Oklahoma Department of Wildlife
12 Conservation or designee;
13 5. One member representing the Division of Agriculture at
14 Oklahoma State University, to be appointed by the Governor;
15 6. Two members representing Tribal Governments, to be appointed
16 by the President Pro-Tempore of the Oklahoma State Senate;
17 7. Two members representing the renewable energy industry, to
18 be appointed by the President Pro-Tempore of the Oklahoma State
19 Senate;
20 8. Two members who are producers of field crops, to be
21 appointed by the President Pro-Tempore of the Oklahoma State Senate;
22 9. Two members associated with the transmission and
23 distribution of electrical energy to be appointed by the Speaker of
24 the Oklahoma House of Representatives;
HB2157 HFLR Page 3
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 10. Two members who are producers of livestock, at least one of
2 whom is actively involved in range management, to be appointed by
3 the Speaker of the Oklahoma House of Representatives;
4 11. One member representing the Rural Utility Service of the
5 United States Department of Agriculture, to be appointed by the
6 Speaker of the Oklahoma House of Representatives; and
7 12. One member representing the forestry industry, to be
8 appointed by the Speaker of the Oklahoma House of Representatives.
9 B. Members of the Committee shall serve without compensation
10 but shall be reimbursed for their actual and necessary expenses as
11 provided in the State Travel Reimbursement Act. The Oklahoma
12 Corporation Commission shall provide space for meetings of the
13 Committee and shall provide other assistance and staffing needs of
14 the Committee.
15 C. The Oklahoma Agrivoltaics Advisory Committee shall:
16 1. Advise and assist the Corporation Commission in preparing
17 any reports required by this section and in conducting the
18 assessment pursuant to Section 4 of this act;
19 2. Identify for Oklahoma agricultural and nonagricultural
20 landowners as well as renewable energy and transmission line
21 developers existing tools and government initiatives designed to
22 help in the siting and construction of renewable energy projects and
23 transmission systems in a manner supportive of farming, ranching,
24 and forestry, including agritourism and outdoor recreation leases;
